abstract: Most experts make New Zealand a heavy favorite to secure a third straight World Cup title, but there are formidable challengers.
snippet: Most experts make New Zealand a heavy favorite to secure a third straight World Cup title, but there are formidable challengers.
lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — The Rugby World Cup, which opens Friday in Tokyo, is likely to be about which of the 19 other teams has the right stuff to knock the two-time defending champion New Zealand All Blacks off their throne.

abstract: Mr. Gillis was dropped by “Saturday Night Live” after making racist comments about Asian-Americans and using a slur to refer to Mr. Yang, a presidential candidate, who has urged forgiveness.
snippet: Mr. Gillis was dropped by “Saturday Night Live” after making racist comments about Asian-Americans and using a slur to refer to Mr. Yang, a presidential candidate, who has urged forgiveness.
lead_paragraph: Shane Gillis, a 31-year-old stand-up comedian who was named last week to the “Saturday Night Live” cast, has mimicked caricatures of Chinese accents. He has called it a “hassle” to have to speak with a waiter in a Chinese restaurant. He has used a racial slur to refer to the entrepreneur Andrew Yang.

abstract: A few days after Gillis was named to the cast, the show said that he would not stay on, and that it had been unaware of his offensive remarks.
snippet: A few days after Gillis was named to the cast, the show said that he would not stay on, and that it had been unaware of his offensive remarks.
lead_paragraph: Shane Gillis, a comedian named last week to the “Saturday Night Live” cast before videos surfaced in which he used slurs and offensive language, will not be joining the show, the program announced on Monday.

snippet: Mr. Sanders has overhauled his New Hampshire state operations, as his campaign fights to maintain support in a state he won by more than 22 percentage points in 2016.
lead_paragraph: Senator Bernie Sanders has overhauled his New Hampshire state operations five months before the primary, as his campaign fights to maintain support in a state he won by more than 22 percentage points in 2016.

abstract: Also this week, Kamala Harris releases a long-awaited plan, Elizabeth Warren wants to expand Social Security, and President Trump has a new Republican challenger.
snippet: Also this week, Kamala Harris releases a long-awaited plan, Elizabeth Warren wants to expand Social Security, and President Trump has a new Republican challenger.
lead_paragraph: A slimmed-down Democratic debate dominated this week’s campaign news — but there were other developments, too. Here’s our weekly catch-up on the 2020 election and the Democratic field.

abstract: What a colleague says he missed the first time.
snippet: What a colleague says he missed the first time.
lead_paragraph: Early last year, Kevin Roose wrote an article about Andrew Yang’s entry into the 2020 presidential campaign. At the time, Yang’s candidacy was quixotic — he was not well known and had never held elected office — and Kevin’s tone was skeptical.
